   Public Information Center

   a lowercase i The FDIC distributes its publications in many ways to
   meet the needs of financial institution professionals, researchers,
   students, reporters, and the general public:
     * FDIC's Mission, Activities and Administrative Actions
     * Manuals, Regulations and Other Guidance for Bankers
     * Consumer Publications
     * Statistical Reports/Analyses
     * Studies on Banking
     * Information for Contractors

   The FDIC's Public Information Center distributes copies of FDIC public
   documents from its office at 801 17th Street, NW, Room 100, Washington,
   DC 20434. Request copies in person, by mail or . . .

   . . . by telephone: (800) 276-6003 / (202) 416-6940
   . . . by fax: (202) 416-2076
   . . . by e-mail: publicinfo@fdic.gov

   The Center is open from 9:00 A.M. - 5:00 P.M. (EST), Monday - Friday.
   Staff also provides reference services, in-house database searching,
   referrals and document reproduction services.

   Most publications are free. FDIC policy manuals have various prices and
   the fees, which must be prepaid. Please contact the Public Information
   Center for more information on available policy manuals and payment
   options. Fees are charged for all materials that must be photocopied
   ($.15 per page) or faxed ($.50 per page). Photocopy orders exceeding
   five documents or 25 pages may require additional processing time.
   Please call in advance for quicker service. Most requests can be filled
   in less than 24 hours.

   FDIC Announcements Listserv

   Subscribe to FDIC-Announce Listserv to receive electronic versions of
   press releases, Financial Institution Letters, speeches and testimony
   as soon as they are published.
